</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> Martin Aspeli &lt;optil...@gmx.net&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-12-22T19:15:00 </POSTDATE>
Hi all,

For Plone 3.1, I'm working on a PLIP (184) which is about the inclusion
of new standard portlets. I'd like some opinions on what you'd like to
see in them.

On the table now are:

1. A &quot;static text&quot; portlet. This has a title (required), a body text
field using the Kupu editor (required), a footer (optional) and a URL
(optional), which if set will turn the header and footer into links.

2. A &quot;collection&quot; portlet. This allows the administrator to find a
Collection (Topic/Smart Folder) and show its contents. You can limit how
many items are displayed, and there'll be a &quot;more...&quot; link in the footer
that links to the underlying collection itself, which you can turn off
with a checkbox.

Now - are there other options you'd like to see for these two portlets?
If so, please justify with some realistic use cases.

Also, if there are other portlets (or modifications to existing
portlets) you miss and feel are a good candidate for inclusion in the
Plone core, please say so. Again, please justify with some real-world
use cases.

I can't promise anything, but consider this your chance to give input! :)

Martin

