Right, exactly.

I don't want any more portlets in plone.app.portlets itself, since that
should be about infrastructure. For Plone 3.1, we'll ship two additional
packages: plone.portlet.static and plone.portlet.collection.

One of the goals of the new portlets infrastructure was to make it
easier to distribute re-usable, configurable portlets. Make an egg,
stick it in the Cheese Shop and plone.org/products, and people can just
install it.

